<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFF50147600EF6D491CB8AD7" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFF50146600EF6D493A38A17" blockId="23.[828,1437,1748,2059]" lastBlockId="24.[151,760,190,309]" lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="23" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF50149600EF6D490CD8DC9" bold="true" box="[828,956,1748,1771]" pageId="23" pageNumber="46">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF5014960F2F6D497978DC9" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[960,1254,1748,1771]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hoplosaenidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF5014960F2F6D497978DC9" box="[960,1254,1748,1771]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="46">Hoplosaenidea abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF50149600EF6F490928C29" author="JACOBY M." box="[828,995,1780,1803]" firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Leyden Museum" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" pagination="9 - 70" part="6" refId="ref31088" refString="JACOBY M. 1884 a: Descriptions of new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera from Sumatra. Notes from the Leyden Museum 6: 9 - 70." title="Descriptions of new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera from Sumatra" type="journal article" year="1884" yearSuffix="a">JACOBY (1884a)</bibRefCitation>
based on female specimens only, which was mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF50149673FF71497C68C09" author="JACOBY M." box="[1037,1207,1812,1835]" firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Leyden Museum" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" pagination="201 - 230" part="6" refId="ref31117" refString="JACOBY M. 1884 b: Description of new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera collected by Dr. B. Hagen at Serdang (East Sumatra). Notes from the Leyden Museum 6: 201 - 230." title="Description of new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera collected by Dr. B. Hagen at Serdang (East Sumatra)" type="journal article" year="1884" yearSuffix="b">JACOBY (1884b)</bibRefCitation>
when describing the males. The males are characterised by modified metatibiae which are flat and extended in the middle. I examined one of the female 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF5014960FFF774975B8CA9" box="[973,1066,1908,1931]" pageId="23" pageNumber="46">syntypes</typeStatus>
in the RMNH. The male specimen labelled as the type deposited in the MZC cannot be considered as a part of the type series as its label data refer to Serdang and thus belongs to the specimens published by 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF50149600EF7F490978329" author="JACOBY M." box="[828,998,2036,2059]" firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Leyden Museum" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" pagination="201 - 230" part="6" refId="ref31117" refString="JACOBY M. 1884 b: Description of new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera collected by Dr. B. Hagen at Serdang (East Sumatra). Notes from the Leyden Museum 6: 201 - 230." title="Description of new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera collected by Dr. B. Hagen at Serdang (East Sumatra)" type="journal article" year="1884" yearSuffix="b">JACOBY (1884b)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF5014960C2F7F4966C8329" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[1008,1309,2036,2059]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hoplosaenidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF5014960C2F7F4966C8329" box="[1008,1309,2036,2059]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="46">Hoplosaenidea abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species variable in colour as was already described by 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFFA01466199F0BE93908BD7" author="JACOBY M." firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="The Entomologist" pageId="24" pageNumber="47" pagination="86 - 89" part="24" refId="ref31358" refString="JACOBY M. 1892: Descriptions of some new species of phytophagous Coleoptera, and synonymic notes. The Entomologist 24 (Supplement): 86 - 89." title="Descriptions of some new species of phytophagous Coleoptera, and synonymic notes" type="journal article" year="1892">JACOBY (1892)</bibRefCitation>
, having the elytra completely orange, completely black, or bicolorous with black basal and orange apical parts.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="84585F48FFFA01476068F0BE91CB8AD7" blockId="24.[828,1437,190,309]" lastBlockId="25.[151,760,190,501]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="24" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFFA01466068F0BE97488BF7" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1895" box="[858,1081,190,213]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wallacei">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFA01466068F0BE97488BF7" box="[858,1081,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="47">Platyxantha wallacei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was completely overlooked by all subsequent authors and thus missing in all catalogues and publications. I examined the 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFFA01466758F0FE97B68A37" box="[1130,1223,254,277]" pageId="24" pageNumber="47">holotype</typeStatus>
(male, 
<figureCitation id="1CDC43CDFFFA01466627F0FE961C8A37" box="[1301,1389,254,277]" captionStart="Figs 105–112" captionStartId="24.[151,188,1945,1964]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,333,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-13@24.[180,1408,333,1921]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs 105–112. Habitus of species excluded from Taumacera. 105 – Fleutiauxia chinensis (Maulik, 1933) (male, syntype); 106 – F. chinensis (female, syntype of F. mutifrons Gressitt &amp; Kimoto, 1963); 107 – Hoplosaenidea abdominalis (Jacoby, 1884) (male, holotype of Platyxantha wallacei Jacoby, 1895); 108 – Hoplosaenidea dohertyi (Jacoby, 1894) (female, syntype); 109 – Hyphaenia balyi (Jacoby, 1895) (female, lectotype); 110 – Pseudoscelida nigrolimbata (Jacoby, 1899) (male, syntype); 111 – Metrioidea grandis (Allard, 1889) (male, syntype of Platyxantha robusta Jacoby, 1895); 112 – Theopella bodjoensis (Duvivier, 1885) (female, syntype of Platyxantha quadraticollis Jacoby, 1896)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4505542/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="47">Fig. 107</figureCitation>
) deposited in the BMNH and it has the same structure of hind legs as is visible on the photographs of the male used by 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFFB014763A5F0DE924F8BD7" author="JACOBY M." box="[151,318,222,245]" firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Leyden Museum" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" pagination="201 - 230" part="6" refId="ref31117" refString="JACOBY M. 1884 b: Description of new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera collected by Dr. B. Hagen at Serdang (East Sumatra). Notes from the Leyden Museum 6: 201 - 230." title="Description of new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera collected by Dr. B. Hagen at Serdang (East Sumatra)" type="journal article" year="1884" yearSuffix="b">JACOBY (1884b)</bibRefCitation>
for the description of males of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFFB014761BBF0DE92268A37" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1884" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hoplosaenidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB014761BBF0DE92268A37" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Hoplosaenidea abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The only difference is in the colouration of the elytra. The 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFFB01476252F11E92CC8A17" box="[352,445,286,309]" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFFB014762D4F11E91BB8A17" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1895" box="[486,714,286,309]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wallacei">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB014762D4F11E91BB8A17" box="[486,714,286,309]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Platyxantha wallacei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has completely black elytra but this is only a colour aberration and thus I synonymize 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFFB014762BCF15E911E8A57" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1895" box="[398,623,350,373]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wallacei">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB014762BCF15E911E8A57" box="[398,623,350,373]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Platyxantha wallacei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFFB0147619EF15E92F18AB7" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1884" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Hoplosaenidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB0147619EF15E92F18AB7" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Hoplosaenidea abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The female specimen deposited in the MCZ and labelled as a type cannot be considered part of the type series as 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFFB0147625CF1BE91648AF7" author="JACOBY M." box="[366,533,446,469]" firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="The Entomologist" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" pagination="105 - 111" part="25" refId="ref31491" refString="JACOBY M. 1895 b: Descriptions of some new species of phytophagous Coleoptera from the East. The Entomologist, 25 (Supplement): 105 - 111." title="Descriptions of some new species of phytophagous Coleoptera from the East" type="journal article" year="1895" yearSuffix="b">JACOBY (1895b)</bibRefCitation>
explicitely described 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFFB014763A5F1DE92088AD7" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1895" box="[151,377,478,501]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wallacei">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFFB014763A5F1DE92088AD7" box="[151,377,478,501]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="48">Platyxantha wallacei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a single male specimen.
</paragraph>
